You only need to iterate across the string halfway, swapping the characters as the indices go towards the middle.  This works for even or odd length strings.
```
Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
System.out.print(&quot;Enter a number:- &quot;);
char[] chars = sc.next().toCharArray();
int len = chars.length;
for (int i = 0; i &lt; len/2; i++) {
     char c1 = chars[i];
     char c2 = chars[len-i-1];
     chars[i] = c2;
     chars[len-i-1] = c1;
}
String s = new String(chars);
System.out.println(s);
```
Or just use the [`reverse()`][1] method included in the [StringBuilder](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/18/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/StringBuilder.html) class.


